                                  "favorite_count": 153,
                                  "favorited": false,
                                  "full_text": "🚨 Do LLMs need to store everything they read in memory?\nTo reduce KV cache size and improve decoding speeds, we propose Self-Pruned KV attention, a mechanism where the model learns to decide which KVs to write in the persistent  KV cache, discarding all the rest! @AIatMeta🧵 https://t.co/5UeHSpusGo",
