                                "favorite_count": 794,
                                "favorited": false,
                                "full_text": "NVIDIA has done the impossible and nobody's talking about it.\n\nThey trained a 12 BILLION parameter LLM in 4-bit precision on 10 trillion tokens.\n\nFor years, the AI industry has been stuck.\n\nIf you wanted to train a world-class AI, you had to use 16-bit or 8-bit precision. Going https://t.co/OGkyz9WDJS",
                                "id_str": "2055130148614050264",
                                "is_quote_status": false,
                                "lang": "en",
                                "possibly_sensitive": false,
                                "possibly_sensitive_editable": true,
                                "quote_count": 17,
                                "reply_count": 39,
                                "retweet_count": 114,
                                "retweeted": false,
                                "user_id_str": "1478392249675300868"
                              },
                              "note_tweet": {
                                "is_expandable": true,
                                "note_tweet_results": {
                                  "result": {
                                    "entity_set": {
                                      "hashtags": [],
                                      "smarttags": [],
                                      "symbols": [],
                                      "urls": [],
                                      "user_mentions": []
                                    },
                                    "id": "Tm90ZVR3ZWV0OjIwNTUxMzAxNDgzNDk4ODY0NjQ=",
                                    "richtext": {
                                      "richtext_tags": []
                                    },
                                    "text": "NVIDIA has done the impossible and nobody's talking about it.\n\nThey trained a 12 BILLION parameter LLM in 4-bit precision on 10 trillion tokens.\n\nFor years, the AI industry has been stuck.\n\nIf you wanted to train a world-class AI, you had to use 16-bit or 8-bit precision. Going lower to 4-bit, was a death sentence for the model. It would become unstable, \"hallucinate\" its own math, and eventually collapse.\n\nBut NVIDIA proved that \"impossible\" was just a math problem.\n\nThey used a new format called NVFP4.\n\nInstead of a standard, rigid structure, NVFP4 uses \"micro-scaling.\" It groups numbers into tiny blocks and applies individual scaling factors to each one. It’s like giving the AI a pair of high-definition glasses for its own data, allowing it to see fine details even with 75% less memory.\n\nThe result is a total paradigm shift:\n\n- 2× to 3× faster arithmetic performance.\n- 50% reduction in memory usage.\n- Near-zero loss in intelligence.\n\nThe researchers compared the 4-bit model against a massive 8-bit baseline. The curves are identical. On MMLU, GSM8K, and coding benchmarks, the \"tiny\" 4-bit version performed within 0.1% of the more expensive model.\n\nThis is an economic earthquake.\n\nTraining a frontier model used to require tens of thousands of GPUs and months of time. NVIDIA just showed we can get the same results with half the hardware and a fraction of the electricity."
                                  }
                                }
                              },
