                            "favorite_count": 38,
                            "favorited": false,
                            "full_text": "If you use Bing Image Creator, you may have noticed that DALL·E 3 will be retiring in the coming weeks.\n\nWe shipped the first version of this model in Bing three years ago. It was the first free image gen model shipped in a product at large scale.\n\nAt the time, many thought image https://t.co/hM4RybeREk",
                            "id_str": "2055387069803815020",
                            "is_quote_status": false,
                            "lang": "en",
                            "possibly_sensitive": false,
                            "possibly_sensitive_editable": true,
                            "quote_count": 0,
                            "reply_count": 3,
                            "retweet_count": 1,
                            "retweeted": false,
                            "user_id_str": "81206529"
                          },
                          "note_tweet": {
                            "is_expandable": true,
                            "note_tweet_results": {
                              "result": {
                                "entity_set": {
                                  "hashtags": [],
                                  "smarttags": [],
                                  "symbols": [],
                                  "urls": [],
                                  "user_mentions": []
                                },
                                "id": "Tm90ZVR3ZWV0OjIwNTUzODcwNjk2OTA2NTg4MTY=",
                                "text": "If you use Bing Image Creator, you may have noticed that DALL·E 3 will be retiring in the coming weeks.\n\nWe shipped the first version of this model in Bing three years ago. It was the first free image gen model shipped in a product at large scale.\n\nAt the time, many thought image gen would not be valuable for mainstream users. But our user research said otherwise, and today it’s a must-have feature in AI products.\n\nAs support for DALL·E 3 winds down, we unfortunately need to retire it. But we know how much this model means to our creator community. \n\nThat's why we're working hard on a dedicated replacement built to preserve the things you love about it, like its overall look and feel.\n\nIn the meantime, give our other models a try – there's a lot to explore. More to share soon and thank you for creating with us."
                              }
                            }
                          },
