                                  "full_text": "Very excited to launch a project I've been helping out with the last couple months.*\n\nThe Center for Shared AI Prosperity is an attempt by an, other than me, very impressive team (so far including @davidshor, @katz_morris, @StefFeldman, @maidinoff, Lindsay Lamont, Jesse https://t.co/lkZkLjWe29",
                                  "id_str": "2055270356970004511",
                                  "is_quote_status": false,
                                  "lang": "en",
                                  "possibly_sensitive": false,
                                  "possibly_sensitive_editable": true,
                                  "quote_count": 31,
                                  "reply_count": 27,
                                  "retweet_count": 116,
                                  "retweeted": false,
                                  "user_id_str": "15950086"
                                },
                                "note_tweet": {
                                  "is_expandable": true,
                                  "note_tweet_results": {
                                    "result": {
                                      "entity_set": {
                                        "hashtags": [],
                                        "smarttags": [],
                                        "symbols": [],
                                        "urls": [
                                          {
                                            "display_url": "csaip.org",
                                            "expanded_url": "https://www.csaip.org/",
                                            "indices": [
                                              1713,
                                              1736
                                            ],
                                            "url": "https://t.co/aCWjgTcYaj"
                                          }
                                        ],
                                        "user_mentions": [
                                          {
                                            "id_str": "9909102",
                                            "indices": [
                                              197,
                                              207
                                            ],
                                            "name": "David Shor",
                                            "screen_name": "davidshor"
                                          },
                                          {
                                            "id_str": "2719289291",
                                            "indices": [
                                              209,
                                              221
                                            ],
                                            "name": "Morris Katz",
                                            "screen_name": "katz_morris"
                                          },
                                          {
                                            "id_str": "363264504",
                                            "indices": [
                                              223,
                                              235
                                            ],
                                            "name": "Stefanie Feldman",
                                            "screen_name": "StefFeldman"
                                          },
                                          {
                                            "id_str": "268463867",
                                            "indices": [
                                              237,
                                              247
                                            ],
                                            "name": "Marc Aidinoff",
                                            "screen_name": "maidinoff"
                                          },
                                          {
                                            "id_str": "6527442",
                                            "indices": [
                                              283,
                                              295
                                            ],
                                            "name": "Josh Hendler",
                                            "screen_name": "joshhendler"
                                          },
                                          {
                                            "id_str": "291",
                                            "indices": [
                                              297,
                                              305
                                            ],
                                            "name": "Jason Goldman",
                                            "screen_name": "goldman"
                                          }
                                        ]
                                      },
                                      "id": "Tm90ZVR3ZWV0OjIwNTUyNzAzNTY3MDE1ODk1MDQ=",
                                      "richtext": {
                                        "richtext_tags": []
                                      },
                                      "text": "Very excited to launch a project I've been helping out with the last couple months.*\n\nThe Center for Shared AI Prosperity is an attempt by an, other than me, very impressive team (so far including @davidshor, @katz_morris, @StefFeldman, @maidinoff, Lindsay Lamont, Jesse Stinebring, @joshhendler, @goldman, and Lilah Penner Brown) to force DC policy elites to take the impending economic impacts of advanced AI more seriously.\n\nWe do not think this is a normal economic shock, though we are deeply uncertain about what kind of economic shock it will be. We could be left with a world of extreme power and wealth concentration, increasing political instability arising from that growing inequality, and deep questions about how to fund governments that have for a century-plus relied on income and payroll taxes.\n\nOur main purpose as an organization is to surface tractable ideas to reform and grow the safety net to meet the moment; to restructure the labor market so workers are still valued and fairly paid; to remake the tax code so that the gains from AI are shared widely; and to experiment with ways of giving average Americans concrete shares in the AI surplus.\n\nTo that end, we're running a Request for Ideas, and we're offering $3,000 for the best proposals. Top ideas will get rigorous polling from Blue Rose Research to see how Americans feel about them.\n\nWe are trying to solicit submissions from a wide pool, and purposefully don't want to just ask the usual think tanks, economists, academics, etc. (Though we want them too!) If you have ideas that you think could be useful, please don't hesitate to apply. Feel free to reach out to me if you have any questions about the program.\n\nRead more here: https://t.co/aCWjgTcYaj\n\n*Obligatory disclaimer: I'm doing this on my personal time, not in my capacity at Coefficient Giving. Nothing I or CSAIP say necessarily reflects CG's views."
                                    }
                                  }
                                },
