                              "is_translatable": false,
                              "legacy": {
                                "bookmark_count": 117,
                                "bookmarked": false,
                                "conversation_id_str": "2055333358629163376",
                                "created_at": "Fri May 15 17:03:53 +0000 2026",
                                "display_text_range": [
                                  0,
                                  280
                                ],
                                "entities": {
                                  "hashtags": [],
                                  "smarttags": [],
                                  "symbols": [],
                                  "timestamps": [],
                                  "urls": [],
                                  "user_mentions": []
                                },
                                "favorite_count": 801,
                                "favorited": false,
                                "full_text": "It pisses me off when Europeans say things like: Eh, the brekkafast? Pfffft. It is noting. One cappuccino. Maybe square of dark-a chocolate. Maybe one biscotti I share-a with mi Nona, and even she say, “Giuseppe, you eat-a like hog in-a the shit. The minute you see-a da biscotti,",
                                "id_str": "2055333358629163376",
                                "is_quote_status": false,
                                "lang": "en",
                                "quote_count": 8,
                                "reply_count": 29,
                                "retweet_count": 48,
                                "retweeted": false,
                                "user_id_str": "1315801673776992256"
                              },
                              "note_tweet": {
                                "is_expandable": true,
                                "note_tweet_results": {
                                  "result": {
                                    "entity_set": {
                                      "hashtags": [],
                                      "smarttags": [],
                                      "symbols": [],
                                      "urls": [],
                                      "user_mentions": []
                                    },
                                    "id": "Tm90ZVR3ZWV0OjIwNTUzMzMzNTg0NjU2ODM0NTY=",
                                    "text": "It pisses me off when Europeans say things like: Eh, the brekkafast? Pfffft. It is noting. One cappuccino. Maybe square of dark-a chocolate. Maybe one biscotti I share-a with mi Nona, and even she say, “Giuseppe, you eat-a like hog in-a the shit. The minute you see-a da biscotti, your face become stupid. Not hungry. Stupid like farm animal hearing the bucket. No more biscotti for you, Giuseppe. It is time to make-a da ravioli for da village. One ravioli for entire village.” We are not like-a you Americans, with the pancake, the syrup, the Costco, the cheese from-a the can—it go spssssht, like this: SPSSSHT—onto what? Onto another cheese? You eat-a the brekkafast from the bucket, in the car, on the way to second brekkafast. This is Tuesday for you. The bread is cake. The cake is brekkafast. The brekkafast is soup. The soup is cereal. The cereal is blue. Why. What is this Costco you love? A city? A man? I do not know. You are always going there. You go to the Costco, you come-a back, you are crying, you don’t know why, you have purchased 40 pounds of shrimp. For what. For who."
                                  }
                                }
                              },
